## Workflow Recipes

**"Just give me the requirements, I'll code myself"**
```
/dx-req-all <ID>
# Review .ai/specs/<id>-*/explain.md, then code manually
```

**"Generate a plan, then execute it"**
```
/dx-req-all <ID>
/dx-plan
/dx-plan-validate
/dx-step-all
/dx-step-build
/dx-pr
```

**"Step through manually, review each step"**
```
/dx-step        # Execute one step
/dx-step-test   # Run tests
/dx-step-review # Review changes
/dx-step-commit # Commit if good
# Repeat for each step
```

**"Answer and fix PR review comments"**
```
/dx-pr-answer   # Research + draft answers for open comments
/dx-pr-fix      # Apply agree-will-fix changes, commit, push, reply
```

**"DoR → BA feedback → share plan (incremental)"**
```
/dx-req-fetch <ID>            # 1. Fetch story from ADO
/dx-req-dor                   # 2. Validate DoR, post checkbox comment to ADO
# ── wait for BA to check items in ADO comment ──
/dx-req-dor                   # 3. Re-run: reads checkboxes, re-validates, posts update
/dx-req-all <ID>              # 4. Skips fetch+dor (done), runs explain → research → share
```

Each step is idempotent — already-completed steps are skipped. Dependency chain:
```
fetch → dor → explain → research → share
              ↻ BA checkbox loop
```

**"Full pipeline start to finish"**
```
/dx-agent-all <ID>
```

## Cross-Repo Tickets

Some tickets require changes in multiple repos. Run the workflow in each repo independently:

```
# In first repo:
/dx-req-all <ID>   # research.md lists other repos involved
/dx-plan           # plans only the changes for THIS repo
/dx-step-all

# Switch to second repo, run same workflow
/dx-req-all <ID>
/dx-plan
/dx-step-all
```

